97static void
98nvkm_gr_vstatus_print(struct nv50_gr *gr, int r,
99 const struct nvkm_bitfield *units, u32 status)
100{
101 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
102 u32 stat = status;
103 u8 mask = 0x00;
104 char msg[64];
105 int i;
106
107 for (i = 0; units[i].name && status; i++) {
108 if ((status & 7) == 1)
109 mask |= (1 << i);
110 status >>= 3;
111 }
112
113 nvkm_snprintbf(msg, sizeof(msg), units, mask);
114 nvkm_error(subdev, "PGRAPH_VSTATUS%d: %08x [%s]\n", r, stat, msg);
115}
116
117int
118g84_gr_tlb_flush(struct nvkm_gr *base)
119{
120 struct nv50_gr *gr = nv50_gr(base);
121 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &gr->base.engine.subdev;
122 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
123 struct nvkm_timer *tmr = device->timer;
124 bool idle, timeout = false;
125 unsigned long flags;
126 char status[128];
127 u64 start;
128 u32 tmp;
129
130 spin_lock_irqsave(&gr->lock, flags);
131 nvkm_mask(device, 0x400500, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
132
133 start = nvkm_timer_read(tmr);
134 do {
135 idle = true;
136
137 for (tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400380); tmp && idle; tmp >>= 3) {
138 if ((tmp & 7) == 1)
139 idle = false;
140 }
141
142 for (tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400384); tmp && idle; tmp >>= 3) {
143 if ((tmp & 7) == 1)
144 idle = false;
145 }
146
147 for (tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400388); tmp && idle; tmp >>= 3) {
148 if ((tmp & 7) == 1)
149 idle = false;
150 }
151 } while (!idle &&
152 !(timeout = nvkm_timer_read(tmr) - start > 2000000000));
153
154 if (timeout) {
155 nvkm_error(subdev, "PGRAPH TLB flush idle timeout fail\n");
156
157 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400700);
158 nvkm_snprintbf(status, sizeof(status), nv50_gr_status, tmp);
159 nvkm_error(subdev, "PGRAPH_STATUS %08x [%s]\n", tmp, status);
160
161 nvkm_gr_vstatus_print(gr, 0, nv50_gr_vstatus_0,
162 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400380));
163 nvkm_gr_vstatus_print(gr, 1, nv50_gr_vstatus_1,
164 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400384));
165 nvkm_gr_vstatus_print(gr, 2, nv50_gr_vstatus_2,
166 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x400388));
167 }
168
169
170 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x100c80, 0x00000001);
171 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
172 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x100c80) & 0x00000001))
173 break;
174 );
175 nvkm_mask(device, 0x400500, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
176 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&gr->lock, flags);
177 return timeout ? -EBUSY : 0;
178}

180static const struct nvkm_gr_func
181g84_gr = {
182 .init = nv50_gr_init,
183 .intr = nv50_gr_intr,
184 .chan_new = nv50_gr_chan_new,
185 .tlb_flush = g84_gr_tlb_flush,
186 .units = nv50_gr_units,
187 .sclass = {
188 { -1, -1, 0x0030, &nv50_gr_object },
189 { -1, -1, 0x502d, &nv50_gr_object },
190 { -1, -1, 0x5039, &nv50_gr_object },
191 { -1, -1, 0x50c0, &nv50_gr_object },
192 { -1, -1, 0x8297, &nv50_gr_object },
193 {}
194 }
195};
196
197int
198g84_gr_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_gr **pgr)
199{
200 return nv50_gr_new_(&g84_gr, device, index, pgr);
201}
